BRIEFING: SORTIES: 7 @ 2140Z PLEASE ACARS DISPATCH WITH INFO IF YOU HAVE FLOW AND ALSO IF YOU ENCOUNTER ICING ON ANY OF YOUR FLTS
THREAT: WX - WINDS WILL REMAIN LIGHT ACROSS THE STATE TODAY AS A FRONT APPROACHES FROM THE NORTHWEST, ALLOWING FOR SEA BREEZES TO DEVELOP AND BRING CLOUDS AND A FEW SHOWERS TO LEEWARD AND INTERIOR AREAS BY THE AFTERNOON. THE COLD FRONT WILL MOVE DOWN THE ISLAND CHAIN LATE TONIGHT THRU TOMORROW BRINGING SHOWERS ALONG ITS BOUNDARY AND NORTHERLY WINDS IN ITS WAKE. VFR CONDS WILL GENERALLY PREVAIL, BUT MVFR WILL BE POSSIBLE IN SHOWERS.
